arch:property.oc:show_val: Fill below Locus 52 in the pool
3.10 m north south -by- 1.45 m east west (exposed).

Locus 55 is the soil below Locus 52 and above the floor at the bottom of the covered pool (Locus 56). The soil is a fine compacted silt/sand (Munsell 7.5 YR 4/4 brown. Many coins found in this locus (nine in total!), as well as four beads, and one marble inscription fragment. This locus had many more architectural fragments than the two loci above it, with many pieces of marble opus sectile and floor tile. Large amounts of pottery, as well as stucco, bone, metal, glass, and olive pits are present. Ash and a small amount of charcoal are in the matrix. This soil locus, and those above it in the pool are the result of dumping, meant to fill in the pool after it went out of use. This is illustrated especially well in this locus, as it slopes from north to south, easily the result of the process of dumping. It is phased to Stage 4, with the covering of the pool and other post-363 alterations to the Complex.
